The paper discusses a hybrid structure that combines human knowledge with hierarchical reinforcement learning, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of deep reinforcement learning and policy gradient methods suggests that the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG) and robotics (cs.RO). The experiment involves navigation and exploration tasks, which could fall under the sub-category of systems and control (cs.SY). Finally, the use of computer vision techniques may also suggest the sub-category of computer vision and pattern recognition (cs.CV).
